Chilean Stocks: Cruz Blanca, Empresas La Polar, Lan Airlines

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-09-29T20:31:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/chilean-stocks-cruz-blanca-empresas-la-polar-empresas-cmpc.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:18 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index closed little changed at 3,901.13. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index declined 1.4 percent to 2,139.71.  Cruz Blanca Salud SA (CRUZBLAN CC) advanced 4.4 percent to
470 pesos. The health services provider was rated “buy” in new
coverage at Bice Inversiones. The shares may reach 645 pesos by
the end of next year, Bice analysts wrote in an e-mailed note.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   surged 14 percent, the
most in three months, to 393.88 pesos. The department-store
operator seeking to avert a second bankruptcy in 12 years is
attracting the interest of prospective local and foreign
“strategic” investors, Santiago-based newspaper Diario
Financiero reported, citing people familiar with the company’s
restructuring process who it didn’t identify.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   slumped 4.5 percent, the biggest
decline on the Ipsa index, to 11,249 pesos.  Latin America ’s
largest carrier has lost 7 percent in the two trading days since
saying it would seek a review of data used by antitrust
regulators to set conditions for the carrier’s takeover of Tam
SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Attwood in Santiago at 
